The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, October 09, 2003  Corporate Briefs																								 Punjab National Bank, Indian Bank, Oriental Bank of Commerce, UTI Bank and Global Trust Bank have joined hands for sharing ATMs under the banner Mitr. Punjab National Bank will act as the settlement bank for the group which will have an ATM network of 1,700, of which UTI Bank will contribute 1,000 ATMs.																								 Inter Gold, a diamond jewellery firm, has launched Swarna Mudra  gold coins with Mandana art motifs  to revive the ancient Indian floor art from Rajasthan.																								 Yahoo India has tied up with Spice Telecom to enable the cellular operators subscribers in Punjab to avail of its mobile facilities.																								 Bangalore-based Harita Infoserve Ltd, an automotive engineering design services company, has been awarded ISO 9001-2000 certification after an audit by TUV Rhineland.																								 The merger of Salzer Textiles with Pioneer Embroideries has been approved by shareholders of both the firms. Shareholders will be entitled to one share of Pioneer for every 25 shares of Salzer. ADVERTISEMENT
